title: Hand me Down Clothes
author: kathryn
text: hand me down clothes hand me down clothes get laughs glasses are a sign of weakness  i don't really care anyways music makes my clothes my headphones make up for style no one knows almost anything about me.  i don't care if i am mysterious.  i've blown off the norm.  i am supposed to be smart and you call me stupid? the norm doesn't work for me.  but someday i'm going to be famous from a major geek company.   and you'll want to work for me.  i will let you anyways.   i guess i've shown you my life.  i don't want your help.  i don't want your pity.  i want you to know that i heard your stabbing words,  that stabbed me like a pillow.   i just imagine my headphones and my bow.  you can't take those away from me.   i know that you probably don't care.  i just want you to know this.   i know this is not involving what you have to say.  but your words are as dull as a midsummer eve sun.  i know you probably don't understand.  but you'll understand later.  you now see the truth,  it's bound you.  you know i am a good actor.  i'm vulnerable,  but i won't admit it to you lest you bound me i've finally got out.  i believe in magic now.  but i don't believe in you.  call me up when you ready to talk.  these are my words.  i've read the poems of others.  they told me to write this i am writing it now.  i've got you at my door now but i'm not done.  i've not yet closed my eyes.
